com.nomicflux.wuwei

Class ST<S,A>

  • Object
    • ST<S,A>
  • Type Parameters:
    S - Type parameter used to unify a chain of ST actions. This should always be hidden from the end user.
    A - Type of the value being passed along
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Applicative<A,ST<S,?>>, Functor<A,ST<S,?>>, Monad<A,ST<S,?>>, MonadRec<A,ST<S,?>>

    public final class ST<S,A>
extends Object
implements MonadRec<A,ST<S,?>>
    MonadRec which allows for actions within a limited scope, to be chained together with monadic or applicative actions and ended with runST(). Intended for internal use to other classes. ST on its own does not provide any effect other than passing the state type parameter S through a chain of computations.
